  "prompt": "What is Foot & Mouth Disease (FMD)?",
  "response": "Foot and Mouth Disease (FMD) is a highly contagious viral infection that primarily affects cloven-hoofed animals such as cattle, pigs, sheep, goats, and other livestock. Here are key details about the disease:\n\n1. Characteristics:\n- Caused by a virus from the Picornaviridae family\n- Spreads rapidly among animals\n- Does not typically infect humans\n- Can cause significant economic losses in agriculture\n\n2. Symptoms in animals:\n- Fever\n- Blisters/ulcers in mouth and on feet/hooves\n- Reduced appetite\n- Decreased milk production\n- Lameness\n- Weight loss\n\n3. Transmission:\n- Direct contact with infected animals\n- Contaminated feed, equipment, or clothing\n- Airborne transmission\n- Can spread through animal products\n\n4. Impact:\n- Major economic concern for livestock industries\n- Can lead to trade restrictions\n- May require mass culling of infected herds\n\n5. Prevention and control:\n- Vaccination\n- Strict biosecurity measures\n- Quarantine of infected animals\n- Controlled animal movement\n- Comprehensive disease surveillance\n\n6. Global prevalence:\n- Common in developing countries\n- Controlled or eradicated in many developed nations\n\nFMD is a serious veterinary concern requiring careful management and prevention strategies.",
